data.enText: a device that is attached to people or objects to make them fall slowly and safely when they are dropped from an aircraft. It consists of a large piece of thin cloth that opens out in the air to form an umbrella shape.

data.chText: 飞机用降落伞空投补给。

data.enText: to jump from an aircraft using a parachute
The pilot was able to parachute to safety.

data.chText: 她经常去从事跳伞活动。

data.enText: to drop sb/sth from an aircraft by parachute

simple_means.memory_skill: para 伞 + chut 降下 + e → 降落的时候给予保护 → 降落伞

tr: rescue equipment consisting of a device that fills with air and retards your fall
jump from an airplane and descend with a parachute

value.def: A parachute is a device which enables a person to jump from an aircraft and float safely to the ground. It consists of a large piece of thin cloth attached to your body by strings.

example.ex: They fell 41,000 ft. before opening their parachutes...
example.tran: 他们下降了41,000英尺后才拉开伞。

example.ex: UN troops could be landed by helicopter or even by parachute.
example.tran: 联合国部队可以乘直升机着陆，甚至可以伞降。

value.def: If a person parachutes or someone parachutes them somewhere, they jump from an aircraft using a parachute.

example.ex: He was a courier for the Polish underground and parachuted into Warsaw...
example.tran: 他是波兰地下组织的情报员，被空降到华沙。

value.def: To parachute something somewhere means to drop it somewhere by parachute.

example.ex: Planes parachuted food, clothing, blankets, medicine and water into  the rugged mountainous border region...
example.tran: 飞机将食品、衣物、毯子、药品和水空投到崎岖多山的边界地区。

example.ex: Supplies were parachuted into the mountains.
example.tran: 补给物资被空投到山区。

value.def: If a person parachutes into an organization or if they are parachuted into it, they are brought in suddenly in order to help it.

example.ex: ...a consultant who parachutes into corporations and helps provide strategic thinking.
example.tran: 空降到公司协助制定战略思想的顾问

example.ex: There was intense speculation 18 months ago that the former foreign secretary might be parachuted into the Scottish Parliament.
example.tran: 18个月前，人们普遍猜测前外交大臣可能会空降至苏格兰议会。

value.tran: （使）空降（指突然从机构外调入）

trans: 金降落伞(规定员工如被解职即可获得大笔补偿金的聘约条款)
